            "html": "<p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">Bodybuilding, in its own term, is a broad field. No doubt, bodybuilders who use natural and synthetic means to bulk up may bestow you with the inspiration you need. But it all depends on your body, food consumption, metabolism rate, and even your workout regime.</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">Before you undertake your journey to bulk up or pump iron, here are the </span><span class=\"q-inline\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; display: inline;\"><a class=\"q-box qu-cursor--pointer qu-hover--textDecoration--underline Link___StyledBox-t2xg9c-0 roKEj\" title=\"www.gqindia.com\" href=\"http://www.gqindia.com/live-well/fitness/5-mistakes-you-are-probably-making-while-building-biceps/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; position: relative; border-radius: inherit; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; background: none;\">bodybuilding tips</a><span class=\"q-inlineBlock qu-verticalAlign--text-bottom\" width=\"16px\" name=\"ExternalLink\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; display: inline-block; width: 16px; height: 16px; flex-shrink: 0; line-height: 0; margin-left: 2px;\"><span class=\"CssComponent__CssInlineComponent-sc-1oskqb9-1 Icon___StyledCssInlineComponent-sc-11tmcw7-0 bxnMMA\"><svg width=\"24px\" height=\"24px\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><g id=\"external_link\" class=\"icon_svg-stroke\" stroke=\"#666\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" fill=\"none\" fill-rule=\"evenodd\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"><polyline points=\"17 13.5 17 19.5 5 19.5 5 7.5 11 7.5\"></polyline><path d=\"M14,4.5 L20,4.5 L20,10.5 M20,4.5 L11,13.5\"></path></g></svg></span></span></span><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\"> you can follow:</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; background: none;\">1.\tSet your goals and expectations</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">It is best to first set your goals and expectations as it will help plan your workout regime. If you are planning to go the long and natural route to bulk up, you will require a long term plan.</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; background: none;\">2.\tEnsure that you get sufficient rest</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">Body building is not easy on your body. You will be pushing it to its limits and stretching it to higher boundaries. With the same amount of energy, you will be punishing your body, you will also need to ensure that it gets sufficient rest to recover. Bodybuilding tips recommend you get at most 6 hours of sleep without any disturbance to ensure that your body is well revitalized for your next workout session.</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; background: none;\">3.\tEat and eat right</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">With a bodybuilding workout, you are forcing your body to build mass. However, at the same time you need to eat a lot to provide your body with fuel for this growth. As a part of the bodybuilding tips, you need to aim for a minimum of 1g of protein per pound of bodyweight. Ensure that you have copious amount of fruit and vegetable serving at every sitting. The best way, to consume food, is to follow a strict diet suited to a bodybuilding regime. At the same time, ensure that you sufficiently hydrate yourself before or after your workouts.</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; background: none;\">4.\tTraining</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">This is the crucial step to bodybuilding. For beginners who want to go about on their own training, look for an authentic source that will provide you with a workout regime that will suit your requirements. Aim for a regime that will provide you long term success, while providing you solid information on each form and technique. You do not want to be ‘THAT’ individual who builds larger muscles without power, only to end up looking like a fool when push comes to a shove. Focus your training on building a strong foundation with the basic movements, before moving to isolation exercises when you’ve built some solid, basic mass and strength.</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; background: none;\">5.\tPersonal trainer versus self-training</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0px; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">Here is the thing, you can find plenty of sources online and through books that will help you in strength training. But bodybuilding tips recommend opting for a decent strength coach, as he or she can observe your body and help you follow a strict regime in terms of your diet and workout. A good coach assesses your basic movement patterns, flexibility, and strength levels before designing a program for you.</span></p>",
