            "html": "<p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">1. Nutrition: Eat plenty of whole foods. Protein isnt as important as its made out to be. Carbs are more important. Keep protein at 0.5*body weight (in Kg). Eat as many carbs as needed till you feel satisfied. Carbs should only come from fruits, vegetables and rice, roots (like yams, potatoes, beets),  lentils, beans, buckwheat and Quinoa. You should want to avoid gluten because wheat has been hybridized too much that its now inflammatory within the human body.</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">2. Sleep. you need to get deep sleep starting early at around 10:00 to 11:00 pm latest. Check your Vitamin D3 and B12 levels. They are important for cellular health and also to get sound sleep and release of HGH when youre sleeping.</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">3. Workouts. High Volume. High volume will build the most size. You can alternate and have strength days in there once in a month. 12 reps only</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">4. Take a day off after working out two days in a row. Take a day off after leg day.</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">5. Eating as frequently as you possibly can. It should be quality nutrition though. Steamed vegetables, rice, quinoa, buckwheat are the best sources in for cooked carbs. For raw carbs, eat bananas, watermelon, oranges and pineapple. Berries for antioxidants and minerals.</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0px; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">6. Make nutmilks at home using a nutmilk bag. Some of the best nutmilks are hemp milk and almond milk.</span></p>",
