            "html": "<p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">I went from fat to fit so I can answer here</span></p><div class=\"q-box qu-mx--n_medium\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><div class=\"CssComponent-sc-1oskqb9-0 QTextImage___StyledCssComponent-sc-1yi3aau-0 ilDNcJ\"><div class=\"q-box unzoomed\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em;\"><img class=\"q-image qu-display--block\" src=\"https://qph.fs.quoracdn.net/main-qimg-d0a2f726833ae7887fb0cea8a0a513d8\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"></div></div></div><p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">-Do cardio every other day</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">-Have a consistent routine that you stick with, that’s the most important. I do an upper body one day(pull-ups, bench press, shoulder press, curls etc), running or squats/deadlifts the next. I always try to do cardio (running) every other day</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">-Take rest days and don’t damage your joints, but also don’t make too many excuses</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">-Sometimes when you’re tired you won’t sant to exercise. Do it anyways. Some of those are the best workouts of my life</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">-Mix compound movements (bench press, pullups, shoulder press) with isolation movements (tricep extensions, bicep curls)</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">-Eat/drink a protein supplement</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">-Do not “dirty bulk”. Eat clean, Whole Foods. Cut added sugar and high fructose corn syrup, as well as added trans fats and fast food. Not only will this help you look cut, but your body will feel better.</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0px; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">Those are the quick, dirty tips I got.</span></p>",
