            "html": "<ul class=\"q-box\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; direction: ltr; overflow-wrap: break-word; list-style: disc; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 2em;\"><li class=\"q-relative\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; position: relative; margin-left: 2em; padding-bottom: 0.7em;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">Master basic compound movements like squats, bench presses, shoulder presses, chin ups/ pull ups, barbell rows, etc. Start off with simple routines like full body workouts or an Upper Body/ Lower Body routine split. </span></li><li class=\"q-relative\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; position: relative; margin-left: 2em; padding-bottom: 0.7em;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">Learn about nutrition. For example learn about your maintance level calories, how a caloric surplus is needed for muscle growth and a caloric deficit is needed for fat loss. </span></li><li class=\"q-relative\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; position: relative; margin-left: 2em; padding-bottom: 0.7em;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">Learn to eat the right </span><span style=\"font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; background: none;\">real</span><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\"> </span><span style=\"font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; background: none;\">foods </span><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">and about </span><span style=\"font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; background: none;\">macronutrients</span><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\"> and what role they play. For example try to get your protein from healthy animal protein sources like chicken or beef. Try to get carbohydrates from sources such as potatoes and rice.</span></li><li class=\"q-relative\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; position: relative; margin-left: 2em; padding-bottom: 0.7em;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">Learn the proper form for any exercise before adding on weight</span></li><li class=\"q-relative\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; position: relative; margin-left: 2em; padding-bottom: 0.7em;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">Focus on using free weights versus machines</span></li><li class=\"q-relative\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; position: relative; margin-left: 2em; padding-bottom: 0px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">Finally the Internet is your friend. There are an incredible amount of exercise tutorials on YouTube, etc. Anything you need to know about weightlifting is online</span></li></ul>",
