            "html": "<p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">This depends on whether or not you want to go natural or geared up. In either case, Testosterone Nation is your premiere source for bodybuilding stuff. </span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">You also have to decide if aesthetics is your goal, or an acceptable side effect, because while bodybuilders, athletes, and powerlifters will ALL have different styles, there will be some aesthetic benefit to all three. (Yes, even powerlifting, the days of fat boy powerlifters are slowly disappearing.)</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0px; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">If you just want to look good naked, seriously consider just doing athletic training like sprinting and cross training with weights. You might not need the severe dieting that bodybuilders do.</span></p>",
